  "materials": "The corridor features a floor of polished **Black Basalt**, perpetually cool to the touch, and load-bearing walls of dark, rough-hewn granite. All doorways are framed by heavy, gilded iron and secured by thick **Reinforced Oak** doors. The western wall is almost entirely covered by thick, blood-red velvet tapestries, hung to dampen sound.",
  "lighting_scheme": "The space is cast in **Dim Light** exclusively by iron sconces holding cold, blue **Gloom Gems**. The gems emit just enough light to prevent total darkness, but they amplify shadows, making the 15ft width feel cavernous and unsafe. No natural light ever penetrates this interior spine.",
  "atmosphere": "The corridor is characterized by an **oppressive silence**. The heavy tapestries absorb sound, giving footsteps a flat, heavy quality. The air is still and cold, carrying a faint metallic tang of dried blood polish, instilling a mood of constant **vigilance and silent dread**—a place where official authority is rarely questioned.",
