  "history": "For centuries, the East Wing Corridor has been the administrative heart of the regime, witnessing every major political shift since the Keep's construction. Its current name, the 'Corridor of Oaths,' dates back two decades, when the paranoid Lord Malakor mandated that all high officials must physically touch the corridor's floor carvings—supposedly blessed with an anti-betrayal curse—upon entering council. The security measures and silent atmosphere are the result of several high-profile assassinations that took place here during the last blood-succession crisis.",
  "current_events": "A high-stakes diplomatic meeting between two rival vampire houses is scheduled for the Council Chamber this evening. Security patrols have been doubled, and guards are operating under 'no tolerance' orders. Captain Varkos is stressed, having just received word that a minor noble vassal was seen loitering near the Great Hall doors, potentially scouting the defenses before the meeting.",
  "adventure_hooks": [
    "**The Diplomatic Pass:** The party must infiltrate the East Wing to recover an item or document vital to the Council meeting before the rival houses arrive, necessitating bypassing the trap plates and patrols.",
    "**The Cursed Oaths:** The party is hired to retrieve a sample of the anti-betrayal floor carving dust for a ritual, which requires disabling the floor traps and chiseling the black basalt without alerting the guards.",
    "**Retrieve the Messenger:** A friendly NPC carrying a plea for help was detained by Captain Varkos in the East Wing and must be quietly extracted before he is interrogated."
  ],
  "special_features": {
    "Anti-Betrayal Stone": "The basalt floor carvings are charged with a weak, ancient protective enchantment. Any non-vampire creature attempting to make a Charisma (Deception) check while standing on the carvings does so with Disadvantage.",
    "The Echo-Dampening Drapes": "The heavy velvet tapestries on the West wall provide cover from noise. When combat begins, the noise is largely contained within the 15ft corridor width, imposing Disadvantage on Perception checks made by creatures outside the corridor to hear the commotion."
  },
  "cinematic_walkthrough": "Stepping through the heavy double doors from the Great Hall, you are immediately plunged into an uneasy silence. The air is cold and heavy, a stark contrast to the vast space you just left. The Corridor of Oaths stretches out before you, an unnervingly straight, 250-foot funnel defined by low-hanging, sound-dampening velvet tapestries that line the wall to your left (West).\n\nOnly the cold, blue light of the Gloom Gems, mounted in grotesque iron sconces, cuts through the gloom. The light is harsh and unforgiving, turning the black basalt floor into a mirror that reflects your own cautious, flattened steps. The silence here is tactical; it forces you to rely entirely on sight, making the deep shadows along the eastern wall—where secured doors lead to the heart of the castle's bureaucracy—feel menacing and filled with unseen eyes.\n\nAs you walk the long passage, you pass recessed guard alcoves, their corners swallowed by darkness. The atmosphere is tense, suggesting that even a whisper would be a violation. This is the spine of authority, and you feel the weight of every oath ever taken (and broken) pressing down on you."
}

